I created an account just to post this: 

@nilax22: do a search you MORON! You managed to find this torrent so how hard is it to find the 64 bit version???

@iru5555: Bravo! Thanks to your spelling I am not even sure if you were asking a question or answering some invisible question, but DUUUUUH! Look at the torrent name: Windows 8 Enterprise RTM. RTM RTM RTM. See it now?

@gunduboss: Just leave. And never ever download any versions of Windows. Just go and buy it from a shop. You have no business whatsoever trying a non-release version of any OS. You'll just kill your computer and go waste your daddy's dollars in order to have someone format it and get it working again.

@x_engine: it's the bootable version. The only non-bootable version was the first leaked version of the Windows 8 Enterprise N-version

@nilax22:

My comment still stands: SEARCH. Can't find it? It doesn't exist. 

@heuir2:

Fine but even if someone DOES manage to crack it, why not just wait a few more days to get the version that actually targets us, non-enterprise users? Plus if you check some websites, including the Win8 wiki, you'll notice that Windows Media Center cannot be installed on Windows Enterprise which could be an early sign that Windows Enterprise won't include this kind of apps (which is actually logical). In any case, I'd rather get the Pro version which won't be bloated with all these extra features that no one will ever need outside an office environment.
